consensus text: in a Barn of his own for some secret purpose
The roof being faulty and admitting rain
water to fall copiously in amongst them
they first began to smoke and at last to
take fire and burn like red hot coals
so that the Town was considerably disturbed
During the fermentation of pyrites with [underline]water[/underline]
sulphur is [underline]evolved[/underline] and the same species of
inflamable air which is given out [deletion]from[/deletion]
but there are other products of [underline]eruption[/underline] which
cannot be generated merely from such a [deletion]caue[/deletion]
